[~sjones], I've used @PreUpdate (and @PrePersist) to annotate code that initializes this column for an already existing record. It doesn't seem to be doing what I intend it to. Am I not using the right annotation here?

{code}
  @PrePersist
  @PreUpdate
  public void updateDefaults() {
    if (this.S3EndpointHeadResponse == null) {
      this.S3EndpointHeadResponse = Integer.valueOf(DEFAULT_S3_HEAD_RESPONSE);
    }
  }
{code}

Commit 87e9a6b9a9287a1bf2ae1532e6605264b9f4081f

After upgrade from released 4.2.2 to latest master, we see the offending property being created and initialized to the right 405 value, for walrus or riakcs. It needs to be manually set to 200 if using ceph-rgw per EUCA-11496.

{noformat}
# euctl objectstorage.s3provider.s3endpointheadresponse
objectstorage.s3provider.s3endpointheadresponse = 405
{noformat}
